miner Kazatomprom plans to spend about 34 billion tenge ($233
million) to build a solar-batteries plant.  The company aims to start construction this month in Astana
and complete it within two years, Chief Executive Officer
Vladimir Shkolnik told members of parliament today, according to
his press office.  The plant will be constructed in partnership with French
companies, Shkolnik said, without elaborating.  To contact the reporter on this story:
